  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian assistance for 422 families at the mid-Atrato river, affected by the armed conflict</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The basic and immediate needs of the affected population will be met, while the situation stabilizes and during the time when state institutions do not assume responsibility. Vulnerable groups of violence and gender-based violence will not be affected and the recruitment of children by armed groups will be prevented. Our partner will serve six (6) different communities, in three rivers: Napipi, Opogado and Medio Atrato. For each one of them, we will have the missionary team and the alliance with the grassroots organization COCOMACIA, which together have already attended  other similar emergencies. In addition, we have the administrative and physical resources and the respect of both armed actors and community leaders, which facilitates quick access and ensures the implementation of the project without delay.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to cover the main needs that have been identified: access to food and nutritional products, access to personal hygiene, emergency shelter, protection and minimum health services. This attention is expected to mitigate the crisis generated by the effects of the confinement of 6 communities and the displacement of the families of Carrillo, while state institutions do not assume responsibility and until the socio-political situation in the region stabilizes.</narrative>
  </description>
